---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Game Modes Overview" description="OpenFront.io FFA, Duos, Trios, Quads, Team, Tournament mode differences.">
  <PageHeader eyebrow="MECHANICS · 10" title="Game Modes Overview" lead="Different modes have different victory conditions, map rotations, and team sizes. Pick the right mode before discussing tactics." />
  <article class="container-prose py-10 prose prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h2>Mode List</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Mode</th><th>Team Size</th><th>Typical Victory</th><th>Focus</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>FFA (Free For All)</td><td>1</td><td>Territory / eliminate all</td><td>Diplomacy, balance, finding allies</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Duos</td><td>2</td><td>Team controls 95% tiles</td><td>Division: diplomacy + main attacker</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Trios</td><td>3</td><td>Team controls 95% tiles</td><td>Multi-front coordination, railway networks most valuable</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Quads</td><td>4</td><td>Team controls 95% tiles</td><td>Continental warfare, coordinated nuclear strikes</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Team</td><td>2v2~8v8</td><td>95% in 5 min / time-based %</td><td>Speed game, early-game decisive</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Tournament</td><td>1v1 / 2v2 etc</td><td>Bracket-based</td><td>Symmetric balanced maps, skill-focused</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>v24: Duos/Trios/Quads added to public lobby rotation (FakeNeo). Team mode auto-balances troop counts.</p>

    <h2>Common Config Toggles</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><code>isAlliancesDisabled</code> — Disable alliances, pure power contest.</li>
      <li><code>isPortsDisabled</code> — No ports (common for land-only maps).</li>
      <li><code>isNukesDisabled</code> — No nukes, longer games.</li>
      <li><code>isSAMsDisabled</code> — No SAM, nuclear dominance.</li>
      <li><code>isPeaceTime</code> — Extended peace period, beginner-friendly.</li>
      <li><code>isWaterNukes</code> — Nukes affect ocean tiles (coastal players beware).</li>
      <li><code>spawnImmunityDuration</code> — Longer spawn immunity, more beginner-friendly.</li>
      <li><code>goldMultiplier</code> — Direct economy scaling.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Mode Selection Guide</h2>
    <Callout type="tip" title="By Experience Level">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>First time</strong>: Single player + Easy/Medium nations, enable <code>isPeaceTime</code> to reduce early rushes.</li>
        <li><strong>Under 10 games</strong>: Duos/Trios with friends, low coordination overhead.</li>
        <li><strong>Interested in diplomacy</strong>: FFA, diplomacy is the core experience.</li>
        <li><strong>Want speed</strong>: Team mode, 5-minute games, pure military no nukes.</li>
      </ul>
    </Callout>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
